@node Top
@top Bookmark-X

Bookmark-X is a fork of Drew Adams' Bookmark-X package, updated for GNU
Emacs 30 and later.  As the original Bookmark-X, Bookmark-X extends the
built-in functionality of @file{bookmark.el} with over 70 bookmark
types, tagging, a rich @file{*Bmkx List*} browse buffer, multiple
bookmark files, region bookmarks, persistent per-bookmark highlighting,
live preview, and more.

This manual is for users of GNU Emacs 30 or later.  It assumes you are
already familiar with the basics of GNU Emacs (buffers, files, keymaps,
the minibuffer).  @xref{Migration}, if you are coming from upstream
Bookmark-X and want a summary of what changed in this fork.

