@section Marking and Flagging
@cindex marking bookmarks
@cindex flagging for deletion

The marking scheme follows Dired conventions:

@multitable @columnfractions .15 .40 .45
@headitem Key @tab Command @tab What it does
@item @kbd{m}     @tab @code{bmkx-list-mark}           @tab Mark this bookmark with @kbd{>}.
@item @kbd{u}     @tab @code{bmkx-list-unmark}         @tab Unmark this bookmark.
@item @kbd{M-m}   @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-mark-all}      @tab Mark all bookmarks.
@item @kbd{U}     @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-unmark-all}    @tab Unmark all (or only @kbd{>}, or only @kbd{D}).
@item @kbd{M-@key{DEL}} @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-unmark-all} @tab Same as @kbd{U}.
@item @kbd{t}     @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-toggle-marks}  @tab Swap marked / unmarked.
@item @kbd{% m}   @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-regexp-mark}   @tab Mark by regexp.
@item @kbd{d} @r{or} @kbd{k} @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-flag-for-deletion} @tab Flag for deletion (@kbd{D}).
@item @kbd{C-d}   @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-flag-for-deletion-backwards} @tab Flag and move up.
@item @kbd{x}     @tab @code{bmkx-list-execute-deletions} @tab Delete all bookmarks flagged @kbd{D}.
@item @kbd{D}     @tab @code{bmkx-bmenu-delete-marked}    @tab Delete all bookmarks marked @kbd{>} (with confirmation).
@end multitable

@cindex @kbd{x} versus @kbd{D}
The pair @kbd{d}/@kbd{x} flags then executes; @kbd{D} deletes the
@kbd{>}-marked bookmarks in one step (after confirmation).

@section Filtering and Showing
@cindex filtering

@table @kbd
@item .
Show all bookmarks (clear any filter).
@item >
Toggle ``show only marked.''
@item <
Toggle ``show only unmarked.''
@item M-t
Toggle the file/buffer location column.
@end table

@subsection Filter by Type
@cindex filter by type

Keys ending in @kbd{S} show only bookmarks of one type; the matching
@kbd{M} keys mark them instead.  Examples:

@example
F S    file/dir bookmarks       A S    autofile bookmarks
B S    non-file bookmarks       Y S    bookmark-file bookmarks
R S    region bookmarks         Z S    bookmark-list bookmarks
I S    Info bookmarks           K S    desktop bookmarks
G S    Gnus bookmarks           V S    variable-list bookmarks
M S    @command{man}-page bookmarks  N S    non-invokable bookmarks
W E S  EWW bookmarks            w S    snippet bookmarks
X S    temporary bookmarks      O S    orphaned local-file bookmarks
# S    autonamed bookmarks      M-d M-s  Dired bookmarks
T S    tagged bookmarks         T U    untagged bookmarks
H S    highlighted bookmarks    - S    omitted bookmarks
@end example

@subsection Incremental Pattern Matching
@cindex incremental filtering

Type @kbd{P PREFIX REGEXP} and the display narrows as you type.  Press
a non-self-inserting key (e.g.@: @key{RET}) to commit.

@table @kbd
@item P B
Filter by bookmark name.
@item P F
Filter by file name.
@item P A
Filter by annotation.
@item P T
Filter by tag.
@end table

@section Omitting (vs. Filtering)
@cindex omitting

Omitting is a stronger form of hiding: omitted bookmarks are hidden
from every view except the dedicated omit view.

@table @kbd
@item - >
@code{bmkx-bmenu-omit/unomit-marked}---move marked to/from the omit list.
@item - S
@code{bmkx-bmenu-show-only-omitted-bookmarks}.
@item - U
@code{bmkx-unomit-all}---can also be invoked outside @file{*Bmkx List*}.
@end table

@section Sorting
@cindex sorting

Repeat @kbd{s s} (@code{bmkx-bmenu-change-sort-order-repeat}) to cycle
through every available sort order.  Or pick one directly:

@multitable @columnfractions .42 .15 .43
@headitem Command @tab Key @tab Sort by
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-bookmark-name}     @tab @kbd{s n}   @tab Bookmark name.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-last-bookmark-access} @tab @kbd{s d} @tab Last bookmark access.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-last-buffer-or-file-access} @tab @kbd{s b} @tab Last buffer/file access.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-bookmark-type}     @tab @kbd{s k}   @tab Bookmark type (kind).
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-file-name}         @tab @kbd{s f n} @tab File name.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-by-creation-time}     @tab @kbd{s 0}   @tab Creation time.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-annotated-before-unannotated} @tab @kbd{s a} @tab Annotated first.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-flagged-before-unflagged} @tab @kbd{s D} @tab Flagged @kbd{D} first.
@item @code{bmkx-bmenu-sort-marked-before-unmarked} @tab @kbd{s >} @tab Marked @kbd{>} first.
@item @code{bmkx-reverse-sort-order}              @tab @kbd{s r}   @tab Reverse direction.
@end multitable

Sorting is governed by option @code{bmkx-sort-comparer}; the built-in
@code{bookmark-sort-flag} is ignored.

@section Editing
